26/05/2010
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Police detained 15 suspected members of Darko Saric's organised crime group on Tuesday (May 25th).
Saric is suspected of smuggling 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America.
Serbia's organised crime prosecutor Miljko Radisavljevic says the arrests are the result of co-operation between Serbian and Slovenian authorities.
Slovenian police also seized large amount of money, drugs and firearms.
(Tanjug, Beta - 25/05/10)
